The paper presents a hardware inference accelerator for Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which falls under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The focus on hardware design and optimization also suggests the category of embedded systems (cs.ET) and systems engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of profile-derived per-layer precisions and precision variability suggests the category of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AR).
